      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MINER MICK (6) wasn't far away at the finish when 5th and beaten only 5 lengths (25.84) at Shepparton. Scored previously at this trip. Has winning claims on his best figures. FLYING ROYCE (4) struggled in tougher grade last start after missing the jump at this track, but prior to that won easily by 5 lengths at this track (29.43) beating Big Watch in a Mix 6/7 H on June 29. Form from his last run is proving strong. Can figure in the finish. REANNA'S PRIDE (3) turned in a better effort at Bendigo last start, finishing third behind Storm Hustler (23.92) in a Grade 4/5. Has the pace to be prominent. Strong form has emerged from her last run. Expected to be in this for a long way. ASTON POLICY (1) is always hard to beat when drawn in this box.",
